#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/kata.md:50
msgid "Step 2: Enter the Kata-ready environment"
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/kata.md:52
msgid ""
"We provide the `asterinas/kata` Docker image, which is based on `asterinas/"
"asterinas` and bundles Kata Containers, the Asterinas guest kernel, and the "
"Kata configuration. The image also provides helper scripts under `/root/kata-"
"containers`. Use the same image in one of the two ways below: End users can "
"run it directly, while kernel developers can mount the Asterinas source tree."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/kata.md:62
msgid "Step 2.1: Prepare Docker arguments"
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/kata.md:64
msgid "Define the following Docker arguments:"
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/kata.md:78
msgid "These flags are required for Kata:"
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/kata.md:80
msgid ""
"`--cgroupns host` shares the host cgroup namespace so that `containerd` "
"inside the container can manage Kata workloads."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/kata.md:82
msgid "`--privileged` is required for KVM and nested container management."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/kata.md:83
msgid ""
"`--device /dev/kvm`, `--device /dev/vhost-net`, and `--device /dev/vhost-"
"vsock` expose the virtualization devices that Kata needs."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/kata.md:87
msgid ""
"`--tmpfs /tmp:exec,...` and `--tmpfs /var/lib/containerd:exec,...` give Kata "
"enough temporary storage space to create containers."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/kata.md:90
